article.headline: Denver 73, Arkansas St. 53
article.story: JONESBORO, Ark. -- Nate Rohnert scored 21 points, Brian Stafford had 18 and Denver beat Arkansas State 73-53 Saturday night, snapping a 43-game road losing streak. Rob Lewis added 16 points and 13 rebounds as the Pioneers (13-14, 8-8 Sun Belt) ended the longest running skid in the nation, dating back to March 2006. Daniel Bryant scored 15 points and JeJuan Brown had 14 for the Red Wolves (13-14, 5-11), who lost their seventh straight.
